Making an Express App

1. create empty folder
2. cd into folder
3. npm init -y
4. npm install express
5. touch index.js
6. Create a .gitignore
7. Put node_modules and .env in .gitignore
8. Git init
9. Git add .
10. Git commit -m "Initial commit"
11. follow the steps in the index.js to create bare bones express app
12. type nodemon or node index.js from the file in terminal to see if the app responds
13. Set up ejs
14. Make a views folder in the top level
15. Set up express layouts let layouts = require('express-ejs-layouts')
16. App.use('layouts')
17. Create layout.ejs in the views folder
18. Create an error.ejs in the views folder
19. Render error.ejs page from the wildcard (catch all) route. res.render('error')
20. Create a static folder then app.use(express.static('static')) in index.js
21. Add style.css or css folder in static folder and link in layout.ejs
22. Make a partials folder inside of views
23. Make a nav.ejs and/or footer.ejs inside the partials folder
24. Include them in the layout.ejs <%- include('partials/nav') %>
25. Add some styles for the nav
26. Create a home.ejs in the views folder, home route in index.js
27. Make a controllers and an auth.js inside of it
28. Make stub routes in the router (auth.js)
29. Include the router in index.js
30. Make an auth folder in the views folder and then create .ejs files for the login/etc